encryption technique?

Client-side encryption
 - act of encrypting data before sending it to S3
 to enable:
 1. Use an AWS key-Managed customer master key
 2. Use a client-side master key
 
 
 KMS-managed master key to enable cliant-side data encryption - provide KMS master key ID to AWS
 
 client side master key for client side encryption: client-side master keys and uncrypted data are never sent to AWS
 
 need to safely manage encryption keys

when upleading an object:
 - S3 encryption client generated a one-time-use symmetric key locally, separate key for each object
 - client encrypts data encryption key using master key you provide
 - client uploads encrypted data to S3 and saves encrypted data key as object metadata
 
when downloading:
 - client downloads encrypted object from S3, using description in metadata, determines which master key to use

 - >> S3 client-side encryption with client-side master key
 
KMS not used because master keys should and unencrypted data shoud not be sent to AWS

